[VS2-332] Collection data modalities

Background:
Data modalities are one of the critical elements required when a Data Collection is built. It must be explicitly defined per study to support the ROAM handover artifact requirements and enable accurate source system mapping.

User Story:
As a Data Consumer Lead, I want to specify data modalities for each study so that data sourcing and access are clearly defined.

Acceptance criteria:
GIVEN an Open Access Collection data modality definition WHEN it is recorded for a Study THEN the associated source path requires input.
GIVEN an Open Access Collection WHEN recording data modalities for it THEN selection of particular data modality that can be included or excluded for each study is enabled.
GIVEN an Open Access Collection WHEN recording data modalities for it THEN selection multiple data modalities for a single Study is enabled.
GIVEN an Open Access Collection WHEN recording data modalities for it THEN no Study has blank data modality record.
